description: 1) Veiled female Personification of Medicine, seated, wearing armor, holds object, wrapped in scroll inscribed MEDICINA. 2) Veiled female Personification of Philosophy, seated, holds two children, each wrapped in scroll inscribed THEORICA and PRACTICA, respectively, representing Personifications of Theoretical Philosophy and Practical Philosophy. 3) Veiled female Personification of War, seated, wearing coat of mail, has on her lap, sheathed sword and shield inscribed CONFLICTVS, and holds two serpents. Base decorated with foliate ornament, half figures of three animals, possibly dogs, as supports and half figures of three lions (?) projecting over the base.
